If you want your function to return possibly `null` you have to add it to the return type.

    postRequest = async &lt;T&gt;(url: string, body: any): Promise&lt;T|null&gt; =&gt; {
    ...
    }

And you don&#39;t need await the return value in an async function, the created promise already handles the awaiting for you:

    return response.json() as T;

Use a [Union Type](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/advanced-types.html#union-types) to signal that either a `Promise&lt;T&gt;` or a `Promise&lt;null&gt;` will be returned:

    postRequest = async &lt;T&gt;(url: string, body: any): Promise&lt;T | null&gt; =&gt; {

Note that the return type is `Promise&lt;T | null&gt;`, which indicates that either `T` or `null` will be used for a resolved promise.

